data.meta_description: Sindh - Wikipedia - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Sindh is one of the four provinces of Pakistan. It is located in the southeast of the country and has a long history dating back to the Indus Valley Civilization around 3000 BC. The province has a population of over 47 million people and its capital and largest city is Karachi, which is also Pakistan's largest city and financial hub. Sindh has a distinct culture that is influenced by Sufism and the province contains several important historical sites from the Indus Valley Civilization era.
